  "prompt": "How do I recover a Yahoo hacked email address?",
  "response": "If your Yahoo email address has been hacked, it's essential to act quickly to recover it and secure your account. Here are steps you can take to recover your Yahoo hacked email address:\n\n1. **Go to Yahoo Account Recovery Page**:\n   Visit the Yahoo Account Recovery page. This can be found at https://login.yahoo.com/forgot.\n\n2. **Enter Your Email Address**:\n   Enter your Yahoo email address or your recovery phone number or email address associated with your account.\n\n3. **Verify Your Identity**:\n   Follow the prompts to verify your identity. Yahoo may ask you to provide answers to security questions, send a verification code to your recovery phone number or email address, or use other methods to confirm your identity.\n\n4. **Reset Your Password**:\n   Once your identity is verified, you will be given the option to reset your password. Choose a strong, unique password that you haven't used before. It's recommended to use a mix of letters, numbers, and special characters.\n\n5. **Secure Your Account**:\n   After resetting your password, take additional steps to secure your account:\n   - **Check Account Settings**: Review your account settings for any unauthorized changes. Ensure that the recovery email and phone number are correct.\n   - **Enable Two-Factor Authentication (2FA)**: This adds an extra layer of security by requiring a second form of verification in addition to your password.\n   - **Review Account Activity**: Check recent account activity for any suspicious actions or unauthorized access.\n\n6. **Contact Yahoo Support**:\n   If you are unable to recover your account using the above steps, contact Yahoo customer support for assistance. They may be able to help you regain access to your account.\n\nIt's also a good idea to scan your computer for malware and viruses to ensure that your system is secure and that there are no malicious programs that could compromise your email account.\n\nRemember to regularly update your passwords and enable security features to protect your email account from future hacking attempts.",
